---
# gh-aw workflow scaffold (creative enhancement §8.4 — adaptive automation).
# Copied into a TARGET repo's .github/aw/board-health.md on request, then
# compiled with `gh aw compile` into a .lock.yml Actions artifact. Runs
# through the ProjectOps safe-output pattern (engineering blueprint §5.1),
# inheriting the same auth and human-in-the-loop gates as the rest of the
# design — staged: true previews the status update instead of posting it,
# until a human reviews the first run.
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 14 * * 1" # weekly, Monday — fuzz the minute before committing to a real repo
  workflow_dispatch:
engine: copilot
safe-outputs:
  create-project-status-update:
    staged: true
---

# Weekly board health check

Read the current state of project board {{PROJECT_URL}} via the GitHub MCP
`projects` toolset. Identify items that have been in the same `Status` for
more than 14 days (stale) and any item past its `Sprint` iteration's end date
that is still open.

Post a project status update (via the `create-project-status-update` safe
output) summarizing: total items, count of stale items with links, and count
of overdue items with links. Do not modify any field values — this workflow
reports, it does not re-route. Re-routing stays a human or an explicit
`/move-to-sprint` IssueOps command (see COMMAND.md).
